Yes. Very interesting times. Regulators, especially in the US, are taking a too blunt approach to a highly exciting tech market. Longer term this is gifting the next wave of tech and financial services to the Asian market/enlightened jurisdictions like Switzerland

Is it a “grey” area? Or in many jurisdictions - “not regulated yet”. We must continue to encourage regulators to truly understand the potential of the token economy, and not overly protect encumbents.
